# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using tools like pyenv. But it's often user-specific:
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you choose to not to share the lock file:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is recommended to be committed.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is recommended to be committed
#.pdm-python
#.pdm-build/

